               <msContents>
                  <summary>Papyrus petition from the Arsinoites (modern name: Fayyum), Egypt. Written by Petosiris, son of Petosiris, priest of the shrine of hawks in Oxyrhyncha. Written against Apollonios, the deputy strategos, or highest official in the region. During a recent visit Apollonios had Pais, the son of Petosiris' older brother, taken to the threshing floor, where they presumably took the priests' provisions away. Petosiris requests that they are restituted so that they can continue feeding and mummifying the hawks. Farewell reads, "Good luck." P.Duk.inv. 714 is another copy(?) of this petition in the same hand</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">Actual dimensions of item are 15.2 x 9.8 cm</note>
                     <note type="general">20 lines</note>
                     <note type="general">Written along the fibers on the recto</note>
                     <note type="general">Lower margin of 1 cm.; left margin of 2 cm.; small right margin</note>
                     <note type="general">P.Duk.inv. 715 was formerly P.Duk.inv. MF79 55</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">In Greek</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
